548
00:29:02,260 --> 00:29:04,763
a door affords opening, floor affords walking,

549
00:29:04,863 --> 00:29:06,265
window affords looking through.

550
00:29:06,545 --> 00:29:07,266
You get the idea.

551
00:29:08,007 --> 00:29:10,568
Now there is such a thing as misperceived affordances.

552
00:29:10,969 --> 00:29:13,110
This is when something looks like it does something,

553
00:29:13,130 --> 00:29:14,090
but it actually doesn't.

554
00:29:14,490 --> 00:29:16,171
So you might have a chair in your video game

555
00:29:16,211 --> 00:29:17,552
that looks like it affords sitting,

556
00:29:17,792 --> 00:29:18,792
but you can't sit in it.

557
00:29:19,453 --> 00:29:22,494
And so obviously in video games, this happens quite a lot

558
00:29:22,974 --> 00:29:24,875
because we pull shapes from the real world,

559
00:29:24,955 --> 00:29:27,616
but we don't copy all the affordances of the real world.

560
00:29:29,489 --> 00:29:33,371
